New Records: Caden Dana became the youngest pitcher in Angels history to win his major league debut at 20 years, 259 days old
Key Match Events: Taylor Ward extended his hitting streak to 12 games with a leadoff homer
Anthony Rendon provided the go-ahead hit with a two-run single in the fifth
Post-Match Reflections: Caden Dana expressed pride in the win and his performance
Ron Washington praised Dana's poise and ability to make key pitches
Miscellaneous Highlights: Dana struck out four and walked four
Dana threw 52 of his 95 pitches for strikes
Ben Joyce worked a scoreless ninth for his fourth save
